Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.60,0:00:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.35,0:00:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.42,0:00:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.64,0:00:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.95,0:00:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.47,0:00:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.41,0:00:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.37,0:01:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.49,0:01:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.72,0:01:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba gave me the card needed to battle against Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.98,0:01:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Devil's Sanctuary!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.69,0:01:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The card allowed me to escape the effects of One Turn Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.24,0:01:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik, it will lead you down the path of defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.63,0:01:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He used Fusion Cancel to get out at the last second?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.38,0:01:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, Devil's Sanctuary is meant to {\b0}defeat{\b1} God and to {\b0}call{\b1} God!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.44,0:01:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come forth! Obelisk!!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.90,0:01:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Direct Attack Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.33,0:02:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Eternal Wall - God Slime"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.63,0:02:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Obelisk's Direct Attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.56,0:02:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you've taken 4000 points\N of damage, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.37,0:02:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Oh yeah!\N You did it, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.33,0:02:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah baby! Malik's only got a little bit of Life left!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.92,0:02:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see Obelisk send Malik flying\N halfway across the stage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.68,0:02:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really makes you feel good,\N you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.44,0:02:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he keeps it up, he'll win in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.40,0:02:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Yugi for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.45,0:02:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this the same Malik we know taking\N an attack from Obelisk head-on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Something's wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.93,0:02:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The face-down card on Malik's field... \NCould it be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.94,0:02:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi... Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.37,0:02:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik purposely took Obelisk's attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.87,0:03:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If that's the case, he could only have two reasons for doing that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.97,0:03:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts... It hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.97,0:03:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One: To trick you into thinking you backed him into a corner, and then cause serious mental damage by revealing otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.74,0:03:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the other reason is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.25,0:03:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with Yugi's face...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.39,0:03:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, what's up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.90,0:03:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's this close to winning, but he looks like he's worried something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.34,0:03:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh {\i1}yes{\i0}, you got me\N {\i1}real damn good{\i0} in that one, Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.64,0:03:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That one {\i1}hurt{\i0}!\N It was {\i1}beyond{\i0} painful!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.66,0:03:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you {\i1}know{\i0}, Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.75,0:03:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the {\i1}only{\i0}\N one who's hurt here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.09,0:03:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure hope you haven't\N forgotten about {\i1}this guy{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.60,0:03:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to that attack, his body is\N being eaten by the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.57,0:03:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.12,0:03:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a {\i1}pitiful fool{\i0} this man was!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.33,0:04:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a Tomb Guardian,\N he's given his whole life to protect\N the Pharaoh's memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.52,0:04:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}this{\i0} is the end result...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destined to die\N by the Pharaoh's own hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.41,0:04:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could {\i1}laugh{\i0} from the irony...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.38,0:04:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.64,0:04:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spiced with the flavor of your hatred,\N he must be a {\i1}delicious{\i0} sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.66,0:04:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.04,0:04:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you attack him any further,\N Malik's dominant half will be killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.43,0:04:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if {\i1}I'm{\i0} defeated, you will \Nbe swallowed by the darkness...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.40,0:04:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still fine up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.78,0:04:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}true{\i0} enemy\N we must defeat at all costs...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.41,0:04:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is Malik's evil heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.17,0:04:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to save Malik's \Ndominant half for Ishizu-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.77,0:04:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be a way to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.61,0:04:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.99,0:04:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But what should I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.13,0:05:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will {\i1}devour{\i0} your spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.64,0:05:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and feed the {\i1}scraps{\i0}\N to the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.11,0:05:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then... I will pay you back\N for the pain Obelisk gave me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.95,0:05:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will give it back to you\N {\i1}twice{\i0} as hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.88,0:05:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.22,0:05:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik let Obelisk attack him because he has another strategy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.35,0:05:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm going to show you\N that I {\b0}let{\b1} you Summon God\N in order to trigger my trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.76,0:05:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ri... shid...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.43,0:05:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rishid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.70,0:05:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.06,0:05:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.69,0:05:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Soon I'll be\N headed to the Dark World...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:06:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Before I do, there's something\N I want to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I disobeyed the laws of my clan\N and committed a terrible sin...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.22,0:06:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Eternal darkness isn't enough to\N punish me for what I did to Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's start with {\b0}your{\b1} bloodbath,\N my dear father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.59,0:06:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stop it...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.48,0:06:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was really the dark side I was\N unaware of that committed the act...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.03,0:06:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it was my heart that\N gave birth to my dark half.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.88,0:06:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My hateful fate...\N My hatred for the Pharaoh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.68,0:06:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A perfect creation for such\N a crude heart like mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.57,0:06:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.94,0:06:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When I went through\N the Ritual of the Tomb Guardians,\N you endured the same pain I did...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.79,0:06:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid, {\b0}help{\b1} me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.84,0:06:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}RISHID!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.96,0:07:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It hurts...! It really hurts...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.01,0:07:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have come to change your bandages...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.60,0:07:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't {\b0}touch{\b1} me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please {\b0}tell{\b1} me, Rishid...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.07,0:07:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who do I {\b0}hate{\b1} for this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.29,0:07:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.34,0:07:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your face...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.26,0:07:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I cannot share the pain that you are suffering from, Lord Malik.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.98,0:07:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then at the very least...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.86,0:07:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I shall swear allegiance to your family with this scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.88,0:07:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid... You made a choice then to\N share my sin and share my destiny...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You decided to live\N with me in the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.41,0:07:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was those feelings you had that helped\N keep my dark side at bay all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.43,0:07:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't know where your soul\N is wandering right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.28,0:08:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But there's no need for you\N to suffer anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.46,0:08:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether I live or die...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whatever the outcome,\N you need to head toward the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.97,0:08:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank you... Rishid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.98,0:08:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, in that attack from Obelisk,\N you certainly took a\N huge chunk of my Life Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.66,0:08:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in that very instant,\N you activated my reverse Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.88,0:08:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! A Trap?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.60,0:08:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible! Traps aren't supposed to work on the gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.86,0:08:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.\N A god won't trigger a Counter Trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.67,0:08:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, this Trap activates\N when I lose {\i1}Life Points{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.89,0:08:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now watch closely!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.18,0:08:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My horrifying trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.90,0:08:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Metal Reflect Slime!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.41,0:09:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Trap Monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.41,0:09:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Slime Token has\N the Reflection Ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.47,0:09:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It becomes a duplicate of the\N Monster that attacks it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.14,0:09:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It becomes a Wall Monster with Attack\N and Defense Points equal to that Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.16,0:09:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A copy of God?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.56,0:09:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's it doing? That's really gross!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.06,0:09:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The slime's starting to change form...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.82,0:09:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's getting bigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.33,0:09:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.58,0:09:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! It's the Eternal Wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.18,0:09:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Slime!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.12,0:10:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's two Obelisks on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.13,0:10:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But one's just some fake slime version!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if it's only got 3000 Defense Points, Obelisk's 4000 Attack Points can take it out easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't believe he\N copied Obelisk so easily...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.20,0:10:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi's gonna beat that impostor in five seconds flat! Right, big brother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.55,0:10:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.55,0:10:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he copied Obelisk for the sole purpose of defending.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.25,0:10:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A God Copy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.80,0:10:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But even with that ability, he can't copy the power of the god...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.77,0:11:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If it's just a Defense Monster, I can easily beat it on my next turn! But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.53,0:11:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I play a reverse card card...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.54,0:11:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.35,0:11:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't have a card in my hand to bring\N Resurrection of the Dead back\N from the Graveyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.28,0:11:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll use God Slime as my wall until I get\N the chance to Summon Ra again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.37,0:11:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I can make Ra appear,\N Obelisk will be wiped out in an instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.64,0:11:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, I'm going to tell you something!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.14,0:11:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The theme of my deck is "Immortality"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.69,0:11:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's designed to bring back God over and\N over again until my enemy is defeated!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.66,0:11:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that includes\N this God Slime as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.76,0:11:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I'll Summon this Monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.64,0:11:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Revival Slime\N in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.24,0:11:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Revival Slime!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.04,0:11:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Monster with regenerative powers\N that gave me a lot of trouble when\N I was fighting the brainwashed doll!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.44,0:12:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can I defeat a god?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Slime even blocks\N redirected attacks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.89,0:12:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Revival Slime reforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.52,0:12:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate\N a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.99,0:12:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.79,0:12:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I polymerize God Slime\N and Revival Slime!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.69,0:12:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fusion between two Slimes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.81,0:12:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the? Isn't it still God Slime?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.78,0:12:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's got to be something\N different about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.91,0:12:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters combined together can't\N attack on the turn they were formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.34,0:12:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn ends with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.85,0:13:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik must have increased the abilities\N of God Slime somehow in that fusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.36,0:13:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.87,0:13:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.38,0:13:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Big Shield Gardna\N in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.89,0:13:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And The Great War God Obelisk,\N attack the God Slime!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.57,0:13:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Hand Crusher!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.63,0:13:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He freakin' did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.14,0:13:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did I beat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.14,0:13:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}God Slime is regenerating itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.44,0:13:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.54,0:13:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.04,0:13:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that God Slime has inherited\N Revival Slime's Regeneration\N Ability after fusing with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.26,0:14:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it has become\N an impenetrable Wall Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be more specific...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.94,0:14:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Immortal God Slime!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.45,0:14:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Immortal God Slime?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.50,0:14:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.67,0:14:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as that slime is there, he won't be able to damage Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.98,0:14:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has to do something about\N that Regeneration Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.03,0:14:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.03,0:14:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.54,0:14:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That damn Malik knew Yugi was going\N to Summon the third god, Obelisk...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.56,0:14:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Taking that attack was all a ploy to get\N the Immortal God Slime on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.75,0:14:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik's terrifying strategy has even\N rendered Obelisk powerless...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.09,0:14:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is there even a way for Yugi\N to turn this around?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.19,0:14:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.48,0:14:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.12,0:14:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik must be using\N the God Slime as a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.25,0:14:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's waiting for a way to get Resurrection of the Dead back into his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.26,0:15:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If he revives Ra,\N Obelisk will be destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.53,0:15:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I get rid of the Slime,\N it won't damage Malik himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.05,0:15:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What can I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.73,0:15:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to {\i1}think{\i0} about, Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.94,0:15:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait until\N the darkness consumes you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.24,0:15:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That{\i0} is your fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.85,0:15:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.68,0:15:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a reverse card, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.69,0:15:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Bowganian in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.21,0:15:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bowganian?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.96,0:15:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as this Monster remains alive\N on the field, it does 300 points of damage\N to my Life Points every turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.54,0:15:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.42,0:15:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.92,0:16:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place a reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.77,0:16:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I sacrifice Big Shield Gardna!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.03,0:16:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Summon Black Magician Girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.13,0:16:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I don't defeat Bowganian this turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.26,0:16:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my Life Points are going to be harmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.81,0:16:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't let my partner suffer anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.40,0:16:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magician Girl! Attack Bowganian!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.58,0:16:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Burning!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.10,0:16:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.06,0:16:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's far enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.23,0:16:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.03,0:16:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Permanent Trap! Defender Slime!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.04,0:16:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to the effects of Defender Slime, all attacks sent to the Monsters on my field will be\N absorbed by the Eternal Wall - God Slime!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.56,0:16:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here! You can have it {\i1}back{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:16:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magician Girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.22,0:17:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I've got the Permanent Trap,\N Defender Slime, on the field,\N none of my Monsters can be defeated!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.90,0:17:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you attack me with Obelisk,\N the Permanent Trap's effects\N will activate immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.96,0:17:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So as long as God Slime\N exists on my field,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.18,0:17:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,myself and my Monsters\N may as well be treated the same as\N having the ability of immortality!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.53,0:17:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.66,0:17:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, before your turn ends,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.13,0:17:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bowganian activates its Special Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.47,0:17:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crossbow Bolt of Hell!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.62,0:17:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.47,0:17:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner, are you alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.14,0:17:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.48,0:17:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't let my partner take any more of this! But what can I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.74,0:17:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey! Looking like that,\N you're still worrying about others?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.96,0:18:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't even bother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.26,0:18:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your fate has already been {\i1}decided{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.93,0:18:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even God...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the Pharaoh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.90,0:18:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are {\i1}powerless{\i0} when faced\N with my untouchable power!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.24,0:18:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that awaits you\N is the entrance to Hell!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.25,0:18:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before long you will all bow before {\i1}me{\i0},\N because {\i1}everyone{\i0} fears their {\i1}death{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.89,0:18:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yu... gi...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.98,0:18:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it all! Can't he do something\N against that stupid slime?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.74,0:18:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi! Pull yourself together!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.54,0:18:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.18,0:18:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yu... gi...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.23,0:18:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, there's no need to hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.86,0:18:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am already prepared to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.70,0:18:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oi, Anzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.21,0:18:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck're you talking\N about out of the blue?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.01,0:18:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crush me along with the evil\N heart I bred inside of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.02,0:18:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anzu...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.61,0:18:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, it's not her! That's Malik!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.03,0:18:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.45,0:18:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu, what's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.25,0:19:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So my dominant persona still had some\N traces of himself hidden inside of her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.72,0:19:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What a persistent fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.27,0:19:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, I swore I would get revenge\N on you for killing my father...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.82,0:19:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I formed the Ghouls\N with the desire to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.29,0:19:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't know the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.26,0:19:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who killed my father was\N my other self inside of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.23,0:19:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! It was {\i1}you{\i0}!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.20,0:19:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Anzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.58,0:19:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, mister "dominant personality"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.55,0:19:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should have realized that\N before this body became {\i1}mine{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.18,0:19:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But {\i1}now{\i0} all you can do is gather up\N all that guilt inside yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.91,0:19:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and take it with you to your {\i1}grave{\i0}\N as you enter {\i1}death{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.04,0:19:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll take {\b0}you{\b1} along {\b0}with{\b1} me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.55,0:19:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.34,0:19:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one{\i0} can destroy me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.48,0:19:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Certainly{\i0} not some deceased Pharaoh!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.57,0:19:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.54,0:19:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a grip, Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.08,0:20:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.34,0:20:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.80,0:20:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishizu!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.64,0:20:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.94,0:20:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.73,0:20:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to do, Malik?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.90,0:20:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.45,0:20:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all I can do now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.12,0:20:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.33,0:20:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you can send my\N dark heart to the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.85,0:20:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is your final test as Pharaoh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.85,0:20:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.52,0:20:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.90,0:20:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And go die in a ditch\N somewhere by yourself, \Nmy "oh so great Dominant Half".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.54,0:20:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no {\i1}way{\i0} for Yugi\N to beat me in this situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.94,0:20:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then... Shall we continue the Duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.74,0:20:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.41,0:20:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.08,0:20:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.30,0:20:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The card that will put\N Resurrection of the Dead\N back into my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.14,0:20:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magical Stone Excavation!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.98,0:20:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Magical Stone Excavation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.78,0:20:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to the effects\N of Magical Stone Excavation,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.67,0:21:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I discard two cards from my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.09,0:21:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and in exchange, add a Magic Card\N from my Graveyard to my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.77,0:21:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without a doubt, the one I pick...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.48,0:21:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.87,0:21:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On my next turn,\N I will Special Summon Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.50,0:21:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I do,\N it will be the {\i1}end{\i0} of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.18,0:21:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.56,0:21:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got to... There has to be a way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.52,0:21:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I know, Partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This will be our last gamble!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.03,0:21:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.04,0:21:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you prepared yet!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.34,0:21:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The darkness of death\N is right in front of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.27,0:21:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he can't beat Malik, Yugi is going to be offered to the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.24,0:22:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he manages to beat Malik, his dominant personality will be offered instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.12,0:22:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless he can find a way to attack Evil Malik while sparing the good one, Yugi won't be able to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.10,0:22:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he Summons Ra again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.52,0:22:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! You have to bare through it, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.36,0:22:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be something you can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.45,0:22:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Obelisk's Anger: Soul Energy MAX"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.21,0:22:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.65,0:22:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.05,0:22:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.66,0:22:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.69,0:23:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.17,0:23:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.49,0:23:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.39,0:23:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.50,0:23:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.97,0:23:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
